    "headline": "Home Price Growth Unexpectedly Slowed in February. Blame High Mortgage Rates.",
    "summary": "Prices in an index tracking 20 of the nation’s large metropolitan areas rose 0.9% from a year ago, according to S&P Cotality Case-Shiller index data.  “Mortgage rates near 6% continue to weigh on affordability and transaction activity, holding nominal price growth below inflation,” Nicholas Godec, S&P Dow Jones Indices’ head of fixed income tradables & commodities, said in a statement.  Whether you notice prices ramping up or dropping depends on where you live, the data show.",
